@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "FAQ";
}

<section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
        <p class="lead">Everything you need to know about CraftPledge.</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:850px;">
        <div class="accordion accordion-cp" id="faqAccordion">

            <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header">
                    <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq1" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="faq1">
                        What is CraftPledge?
                    </button>
                </h2>
                <div id="faq1" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                    <div class="accordion-body">
                        CraftPledge is a certification mark for human-made work. We provide a trusted, verifiable way
                        for creators and businesses to demonstrate that their products and services are genuinely
                        made by humans &mdash; with transparency about how AI may or may not have been involved in
                        the process.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header">
                    <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq2" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq2">
                        How does certification work?
                    </button>
                </h2>
                <div id="faq2" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                    <div class="accordion-body">
                        Creators and businesses apply for certification by selecting the tier that honestly reflects
                        their process (Craft Assisted, Craft Verified, or Craft Pure). They submit information about
                        how their work is made, which is reviewed through our verification process. Once approved,
                        they receive the CraftPledge mark for their tier level and can display it on their products
                        and marketing materials.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header">
                    <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq3" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq3">
                        What counts as &ldquo;AI&rdquo;?
                    </button>
                </h2>
                <div id="faq3" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                    <div class="accordion-body">
                        For the purposes of CraftPledge certification, &ldquo;AI&rdquo; refers to generative artificial
                        intelligence systems &mdash; tools that can create text, images, code, music, or other content
                        based on prompts or inputs. This includes large language models, image generators, code
                        completion tools, and similar systems. Traditional software tools (calculators, spell-checkers,
                        design software, compilers) are not considered AI in our framework.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header">
                    <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq4" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq4">
                        Can I use spell-check / grammar tools and still be certified?
                    </button>
                </h2>
                <div id="faq4" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                    <div class="accordion-body">
                        Yes. Traditional spell-checkers, grammar tools, and basic autocorrect are not considered
                        generative AI for the purposes of CraftPledge certification. These tools assist with
                        mechanical accuracy but do not generate creative content. However, AI-powered writing
                        assistants that suggest or rewrite entire sentences or paragraphs would be considered AI
                        usage and would place your work in the Craft Assisted tier.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header">
                    <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq5" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq5">
                        What&rsquo;s the difference between the tiers?
                    </button>
                </h2>
                <div id="faq5" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                    <div class="accordion-body">
                        <strong>Craft Assisted:</strong> AI may have been used as a supporting tool, but a human led
                        the process and takes responsibility for the output.<br /><br />
                        <strong>Craft Verified:</strong> No generative AI was used in creating the final product or
                        service. It was conceived and created entirely by humans.<br /><br />
                        <strong>Craft Pure:</strong> No AI was used anywhere in the entire supply chain, from sourcing
                        to delivery. This is the most rigorous standard.<br /><br />
                        Visit our <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="Tiers">Pledge page</a> for full details on each tier.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header">
                    <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq6" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq6">
                        How much does certification cost?
                    </button>
                </h2>
                <div id="faq6" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                    <div class="accordion-body">
                        We are currently in the early stages of building CraftPledge and are developing our pricing
                        model. Our goal is to make certification accessible to independent creators, small businesses,
                        and large organisations alike. Pricing details will be announced as we approach our public
                        launch. Sign up to be notified when applications open.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header">
                    <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq7" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq7">
                        How do you verify claims?
                    </button>
                </h2>
                <div id="faq7" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                    <div class="accordion-body">
                        Our verification process combines self-declaration with auditing and accountability measures.
                        Creators provide detailed information about their production process, and we use a combination
                        of documentation review, spot checks, and community reporting to ensure accuracy. The specifics
                        vary by tier level &mdash; higher tiers require more rigorous documentation. We are also
                        developing technological solutions to support the verification process.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header">
                    <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq8" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq8">
                        What happens if someone breaks the pledge?
                    </button>
                </h2>
                <div id="faq8" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                    <div class="accordion-body">
                        Trust is the foundation of CraftPledge. If a certified creator or business is found to have
                        misrepresented their use of AI, they face decertification and public removal from the
                        CraftPledge directory. We take violations seriously because the entire value of the mark
                        depends on its integrity. We also provide a process for creators to voluntarily update their
                        tier if their process changes.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header">
                    <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq9" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq9">
                        Is CraftPledge anti-technology?
                    </button>
                </h2>
                <div id="faq9" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                    <div class="accordion-body">
                        Absolutely not. CraftPledge is pro-transparency. We believe technology and AI have incredible
                        potential to help humanity. What we oppose is the invisibility of AI usage &mdash; the inability
                        of consumers to know whether what they&rsquo;re buying was made by a human or generated by a
                        machine. Our Craft Assisted tier explicitly recognises that AI can be a valuable tool when a
                        human is in charge. We are not against AI; we are for honesty. In fact, we used AI tools to
                        help build this very website &mdash; and we&rsquo;re
                        <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="OurStory">completely transparent about it</a>.
                        That&rsquo;s kind of the whole point.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
                <h2 class="accordion-header">
                    <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq10" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq10">
                        How do I apply?
                    </button>
                </h2>
                <div id="faq10" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                    <div class="accordion-body">
                        CraftPledge is currently in development. We are building our certification platform and
                        verification processes. If you&rsquo;re interested in being among the first to receive
                        CraftPledge certification, we&rsquo;d love to hear from you. Watch this space for updates
                        on when applications open, or visit our
                        <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="ForCreators">For Creators</a> page to learn more about
                        what certification involves.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="cta-section">
    <div class="container">
        <h2>Still have questions?</h2>
        <p>We&rsquo;re building CraftPledge in the open. Reach out and we&rsquo;ll be happy to help.</p>
        <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="ForCreators" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg me-2">For Creators</a>
        <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="ForConsumers" class="btn btn-outline-light btn-lg">For Consumers</a>
    </div>
</section>
